  DIRL [Dn:][path>][filename] ..

Low Memory

Lists files on drive Dn: using the
given path and file name pattern. If
no pattern is supplied, all files in
the directory will be listed.

In contrast to the DIR command,
neither the volume or directory header
nor the free sector count are shown.
In addition, protected files and
folders are marked with a leading
* symbol, and the modification time
is shown including seconds.
